            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_002121_0001" n="0001"/><!-- Change both @facs and @n -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent small"><add place="inline" rend="gray" hand="#U">Acc 7237</add> <space extent="2" unit="words"/><add place="inline" rend="gray" hand="#U">149</add></p>
<lb/><p rend="italic no-indent small gray"><space extent="1" unit="words"/><placeName>Newstead Abbey</placeName>,
<lb/><space extent="1" unit="words"/><placeName>Mansfield</placeName>, <placeName>Notts.</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><date when="1864-11-24">24 Nov <hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> 1864</date></p><!-- I guess this is 1857, but can we double check?  It doesn't look like it to me. SF --><!-- Fixed. AW -->
<lb/>    
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear Sir</p>

<lb/><p>I thank you
<lb/>very much for
<lb/>your kind invitation
<lb/>to dinner on <date when="1864-11-28">Monday</date><!-- Any way of figuring out the date for this? SF --><!-- Done! -->
<lb/>but I am still 
<lb/>busy at my work
<lb/>here and sorry
<lb/>that it does not
<lb/>permit my going
<lb/>South - I also

	<pb facs="liv_002121_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>thank you for 
<lb/>kindly writing on
<lb/>behalf of my son
<lb/>to <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Sherman</persName> -
<lb/>your friend adopts
<lb/>the line we sometimes 
<lb/>had a smile over
<lb/>in <placeName><country>Africa</country></placeName> - several
<lb/>friends would write
<lb/>so many <add place="below">^</add> <add place="above">other</add> friends 
<lb/>must have given 
<lb/>you the news that
<lb/>I need not go into
<lb/>particulars - Or 
<lb/>I would have sent

	<pb facs="liv_002121_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>you the new book <add place="above" rend="gray small">150</add>
<lb/>but feel certain that
<lb/>some other of your
<lb/>numerous friends 
<lb/>must have sent
<lb/>it - the upshot
<lb/>was we neither
<lb/>got the news nor
<lb/>the book - however
<lb/>I thank you for 
<lb/>so far as you were
<lb/>concerned doing
<lb/>what you could
<lb/>and am &amp;
<lb/><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p> 

	<pb facs="liv_002121_0004" n="0004"/> <!--not sure this page belongs--><!-- OK. AW -->
<lb/><p>You asked in one
<lb/>of your notes what
<lb/>took another son
<lb/>into the <orgName>Federal Army</orgName>
<lb/>He says he was 
<lb/>kidnapped - and 
<lb/>his refraining from 
<lb/>taking life even in 
<lb/>the frenzy of a 
<lb/>charge <choice><orig>shews</orig><reg>shows</reg></choice> that
<lb/>he is there against
<lb/>his will - <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Adams</persName>
<lb/>was here to lunch one
<lb/>day &amp; I had a promise
<lb/>that he would do what 
<lb/>he could - this makes
<lb/>me anxious for his brother</p>

	<pb facs="liv_002121_0005" n="0005"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><persName>R.M. Smith <choice><abbr>Esq.</abbr><expan>Esquire</expan></choice></persName>
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><placeName>4 Bellvue Crescent</placeName>
<lb/><space extent="5" unit="chars"/><placeName><settlement type="city">Edinburgh</settlement></placeName>
<lb/><seg rend="small"><persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> <choice><abbr>L</abbr><expan>Livingstone</expan></choice></persName></seg></p>


